    "title": "Integrative Close: Plant Room Installation",
    "objective": "Evaluate the learner's ability to justify the choice of a specific circuit type and wiring system for a multi-use building containing both office (commercial) and plant room (industrial) areas.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "In a multi-use building, you often transition between different environments. A commercial office might use standard trunking, but the basement plant room—housing the main heating boilers—is treated as an industrial environment due to the risk of mechanical impact and moisture.",
      "When a single piece of high-power equipment like a boiler requires its own dedicated supply, the circuit configuration must reflect that it is a 'dead-end' run from the distribution board.",
      "The wiring system chosen must be robust enough to withstand the physical rigours of a plant room, where tools are used and heavy equipment is moved."
    ],
    "questionText": "You are installing a dedicated supply for a large central heating boiler in a basement plant room. Considering this is a single high-power load in an industrial-style environment with a high risk of mechanical damage, name the required circuit type and the specific armoured wiring system that should be used.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Radial circuit",
      "SWA",
      "Steel Wire Armoured",
      "Radial",
      "Steel Wire Armoured cable"
    ],
    "hint": "Think of the circuit type that runs directly to one appliance, and the specific cable type that uses a layer of steel for heavy-duty protection."
  }
